                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12921727" author="lars_francke" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 18:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot: Can anyone contact KayKay? He did the maven stuff for the Thrift guys with ant plugins (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-363&quot; title=&quot;Maven Deploy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Unfortunately no one can figure out how to use them &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve tried sending him an email but got no reply so far.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be best if we could get Thrift into an official repository.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921739" author="ryanobjc" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 19:18:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A report from a user leads me to believe that thrift 0.5.0 is not compatible&lt;br/&gt;
with 0.2.0... do you know if this is true?&lt;br/&gt;
0.3 but 0.5 has a lot of improvements so that would be the best.&lt;br/&gt;
the current Thrift interface and fix the implementation (byte[] -&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
ByteBuffer).&lt;br/&gt;
need to do our current workaround again unfortunately and upload it to a&lt;br/&gt;
repository. That would be Ryan&apos;s I think?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921745" author="tlipcon" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 19:44:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, 0.5.0 is not API-compatible on the Java side with previous versions. But it is wire-compatible with all versions since about early 2007. Doing the port is pretty simple - just swapping out byte[] for ByteBuffer like you said.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921747" author="lars_francke" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 19:46:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I know -&#160;but that is only from what I&apos;ve read on the thrift mailing lists - the versions should be compatible but I might be wrong. What have you heard? I&apos;ll go and ask on the mailing list and report back here but Todd being a committer might have some insight? We&apos;d want to upgrade to 0.3 for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2155&quot; title=&quot;Add the option to bind to a specific IP address to the Nonblocking Thrift servers&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2155&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2155&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921751" author="stack" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 20:13:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wrote him too.  Lets go to 0.5 if we can?  Want help Lars?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921755" author="lars_francke" created="Sat, 16 Oct 2010 20:19:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the current lib built from the release tarball.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Stack I think I&apos;m good. Will upload a patch for the old Thrift interface later today.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12921872" author="lars_francke" created="Sun, 17 Oct 2010 17:33:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This changes everything to ByteBuffer. All tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m using .array() which should be fine for this Thrift version at least but if that&apos;s not the way to do it I&apos;m all open for suggestions. This is new to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994090" author="larsgeorge" created="Sun, 13 Feb 2011 12:58:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update to 0.6.0 of Thrift?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004996" author="moazreyad" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 08:58:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I created a patch for updating to Thrift 0.6.0. I will upload it (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3117&quot; title=&quot;Update Thrift to 0.5 version&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3117&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3117&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.3.patch.zip). But it is better if it is checked again by someone before making it public.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004997" author="moazreyad" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 08:59:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for updating to Thrift 0.6.0. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13004998" author="moazreyad" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 09:00:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for updating to Thrift 0.6.0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13005288" author="ryanobjc" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 19:51:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;we are on thrift 0.5.0 for trunk, there is a &apos;libthrift&apos; in the apache repo.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We want to get away from using a people.apache.org repo, so I&apos;d like to see thrift 0.6.0 get into apache repo before we upgrade.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I hear thrift 0.6.0 has good things for C++ client libraries, but our use of thrift 0.5.0 on the server side should not prevent clients from using any version of thrift they wish. What other advantages of thrift 0.6.0 would we get on the server side?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13005767" author="moazreyad" created="Fri, 11 Mar 2011 18:22:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I do not know about the advantages except that it is the latest version. In fact Thrift 0.6.0 is the first version I used. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By the way, the name of this issue is a little generic because the &apos;current version&apos; is not defined. May be it is better to change the name to something like &quot;Update Thrift to 0.6.0&quot; so that the issue can be marked as resolved after this specific update. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006078" author="stack" created="Sat, 12 Mar 2011 19:41:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Changed subject to refer to 0.5 version at Moaz&apos;s prompting.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006080" author="stack" created="Sat, 12 Mar 2011 19:43:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was going to resolve this issue because it looks like trunk is up to 0.5 thrift but then I saw this in the pom:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &amp;lt;repository&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;id&amp;gt;temp-thrift&amp;lt;/id&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;name&amp;gt;Thrift 0.2.0&amp;lt;/name&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;url&amp;gt;http:&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;//people.apache.org/~rawson/repo/&amp;lt;/url&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;      &amp;lt;snapshots&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;enabled&amp;gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;/enabled&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;/snapshots&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;releases&amp;gt;
        &amp;lt;enabled&amp;gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&amp;lt;/enabled&amp;gt;
      &amp;lt;/releases&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;/repository&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks like that needs some clean up before we can close out this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006082" author="stack" created="Sat, 12 Mar 2011 19:47:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Moaz I moved the 0.6 upgrade over to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3629&quot; title=&quot;Update our thrift to 0.6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3629&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3629&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.  Want to apply your patches there?  Is 0.6 available in a mvn repo anywhere?  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13006155" author="moazreyad" created="Sun, 13 Mar 2011 07:47:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I couldn&apos;t find a maven repository for thrift 0.6.0. I will update the patch in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3629&quot; title=&quot;Update our thrift to 0.6&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3629&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3629&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; when I found one available.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13007882" author="hudson" created="Thu, 17 Mar 2011 10:33:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #1792 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1792/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1792/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13029181" author="stack" created="Thu, 5 May 2011 06:45:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;TRUNK is on 0.6 now.  Resolving as fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
